  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Medical Assessment Form (MAF) for Refugees Submitted for Resettlement from Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM will conduct 100 health assessments for refugees who are being considered for resettlement on medical grounds and complete the medical assessment forms (MAFs) since the health condition presents a significant obstacle to leading a normal life and achieving self-sufficiency. The impact of this component will be to support UNHCR in the referral process of refugees for resettlement and therefore seeking durable solutions for vulnerable refugees. In accordance with UNHCR&#x2019;s Age, Gender and Diversity Policy 2018, the project/program incorporates and addresses the different needs and capacities of women, men, boys and girls of diverse backgrounds, and ensure that these diverse groups have access to relevant information and are able to engage meaningfully and are consulted on protection, assistance and solutions.</narrative>
  </description>
